## Wrapping it up in a function

interactive_table <- function(data) {
  DT::datatable(
    {{ data }},
    extensions = c("ColReorder", "Buttons"), options = list(
      colReorder = TRUE,
      dom = "Bfrtip",
      buttons = c("copy", "csv", "excel"),
      searchHighlight = TRUE
    ),
    filter = "top"
  )
}

interactive_table(CPI2)

Using searh panes

library(DT)
datatable(
  iris,
  options = list(dom = "Pfrtip", columnDefs = list(list(
    searchPanes = list(show = FALSE), targets = 1:4
  ))),
  extensions = c("Select", "SearchPanes"),
  selection = "none"
)
datatable(
  CPI2,
  extensions = c("ColReorder", "Buttons", "Select", "SearchPanes"), options = list(
    colReorder = TRUE,
    dom = "Pfrtip", dom = "Bfrtip",
    columnDefs = list(list(
    searchPanes = list(show = FALSE), targets = 1:6
  )),
    buttons = c("copy", "csv", "excel"),
  dom = 'Bfrtip',
    searchHighlight = TRUE
  ),
  filter = "top",
  selection = "none"
)
